      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Adelaide ¶ 29th Decr 1886. ¶ Baron Von Mueller KCMG &amp;c &amp;c ¶ Melbourne ¶ Dear Sir,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">86.12.29a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From David Lindsay</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.200/1, item 1, letter book, pp. 410-11, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Adelaide</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">29th Decr 1886.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Von Mueller KCMG &amp;c &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your letter of the 21st inst<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to D. Lindsay, 21 December 1886.</p>
               </note> duly received for which many thanks. I do not hold <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">any</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">one</hi>
               </seg> responsible for the unfortunate choice of a botanical collector for my late expedition. That arrangement was purely private between him and me, his voluntary offer to accompany me was called forth by seeing the press notice of my intended trip.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See D. Lindsay to M, 21 October 1885 (in this edition as <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>85.10.21c).</p>
               </note> That he (Lt Dittrich) is now without funds is no fault [or bus]iness<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS is water damaged. All following […] have the same meaning.</p>
               </note> of mine — he volunteered to go for no payment and he has himself to thank for the [position he n]ow is in. I fail to see his right to b[…]<seg> </seg>with any claim for the […] or any […] sum — That sum was promised […] should succeed in obtaining a […] new pl[…] […]ned to the Govt here and to the G[…] that you had graciously promised £20.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See D. Lindsay to M, 21 October 1885 (in this edition as <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>85-10-21c), where he says he used M's gift to spur the government of SA into granting him some funds.</p>
               </note> […] £45 out of pocket (besides […] [)] I beg of you to put [Lt] Dittr[ich] […]ion and, as you have […]ly considered the collection worth something and further seeing that two new plants were discovered, pay me the balance now in your hand of the amount you have decided to pay for the collection.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I consider Lieut. Dittrich quite unjustified in applying to you for the money which was promised to me.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Pardon me for writing so plainly but I feel that your extreme kindness of heart has led you to consider this matter from a wrong point of view.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to D. Lindsay, 14 December 1886 (in this edition as <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>86-12-14a), and 11 February 1887 (in this edition as <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>87-02-11a).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I shall indeed be proud of the honor of having a plant named after me.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to D. Lindsay, 21 December 1886.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The box of plants will not be opened by the Minister of Education until after the holidays.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With the compliments of the season</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I am</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours very sincerely</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>David Lindsay FRGSA</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Explorer &amp; Surveyor</p>
         </div>
